oracle.apps.fnd.applcore.customization.globalmenu
Class GlobalMenuItemBean

java.lang.Object
  oracle.apps.fnd.applcore.customization.globalmenu.GlobalMenuItemBean

public class GlobalMenuItemBean
extends java.lang.Object

This class contains all the methods necessary to add/update/delete menu nodes from the root_menu and homepage_menu xml file deltas as part of menu customization. The positioning of the customizations within the files is also controlled by this class. The javadoc for each methods explains how this will be achieved. Validation that will cause an exception to be thrown by the manipulation of the DOM documents are the only validation done by this API. Business rule validation is the responsibility of the calling program.

setRendered

public void setRendered(boolean rendered)
Set the value of the redered attribute. The getRendered method on the menu node returns a boolean value, evaluated from either 'true' or 'false' in the menu xml or the evaluated value of an EL statement. This method allows you set the boolean value, but to get the text value you need to use the menu node getAttributeValueRaw("rendered") method. This is used in the getRenderedEL method. Once an EL statement has been used and you wish to clear the EL statement and go back to using a true or false value which can be controlled by a boolean checkbox you need to reset the menu item by using the setRenderedEL method. Your UI should ensure that once EL is set it must use the EL editor to unset it. This is in line with what composer and 'Manage Menu Customization' does today.

Parameters:
rendered -

setNextId

public void setNextId(java.lang.String nextId)
The set method for the nextId variable. This value is used to determine where in the menu hierachy a new menu item is added during customization. If the nextId is set the new menu item will be inserted immediately before the nextId position in the DOM. The nextId is the best position to use if you are trying to add the new node to the top of the list of children in the folder.

setParentId

public void setParentId(java.lang.String parentId)
The set method for the parentId variable. The parentId variable is used to tell the API where in the list of menu nodes to begin an action. For this API the parentId will evaluate to an FndGroupNode (Folder). If nextId or prevId is not set in the bean the API will for addMenuItem - do an appendChild(menuNode). For updateMenuItem - the position in the node tree to look for the id to be updated. For deleteMenuItem - the position in the node tree to look for the id to be deleted. For moveMenuItem - the position in the node tree to look/place the id to be moved. For reorderMenuItems - the position in the node tree of the list of ids' to me reordered.

Parameters:
parentId -

setUrlType

public void setUrlType(GlobalMenuURLType urlType)
The set method for the urlType variable. The GlobalMenuURLType is an enumeration that determines what type of URL is being created. The urlType is used to determine what fields should be rendered in the Manage Menu Customizations UI in FSM. It is also used to determine what if any validation should be use prior to add/update of menu item. urlType GROUP - A group or folder node, urlType APPLINK - Application Page Link (label, rendered, focusViewId, webApp are required values), urlType DYNAMICLINK - Dynamic Link (label, rendered, webApp, webAppDestination are required values), urlType STATICLINK - Static Link (label, rendered, destination are required values), this is also used for secured token link. urlType FUSECARD - Fuse Card to support FUSE+ (label, rendered, focusViewId(some specific value), icon, cardIcon, taskMenuSource are required values), Note! this value must be set for all CRUD operations.

Parameters:
urlType -

getUrlType

public GlobalMenuURLType getUrlType()
The set method for the urlType variable. The GlobalMenuURLType is an enumeration that determines what type of URL is being created. The urlType is used to determine what fields should be rendered in the Manage Menu Customizations UI in FSM. It is also used to determine what if any validation should be use prior to add/update of menu item. urlType GROUP - A group or folder node, urlType APPLINK - Application Page Link (label, rendered, focusViewId, webApp are required values), urlType DYNAMICLINK - Dynamic Link (label, rendered, webApp, webAppDestination are required values), urlType STATICLINK - Static Link (label, rendered, destination are required values), this is also used for secured token link. urlType FUSECARD - Fuse Card to support FUSE+ (label, rendered, focusViewId(some specific value), icon, cardIcon, taskMenuSource are required values), Note! this value must be set for all CRUD operations.

Returns:
GlobalMenuURLType

setMenuType

public void setMenuType(GlobalMenuType menuType)
The set method for the menuType variable. The menuType is used to tell the API what global menu file this menu item should be added to. It is currently used in Navigator Menu customization UI, but may be used for the batch insert operations that may be required for migration. Or batch customzation in the future. To lessen the impact of change this has been added for future use. The types are: NAVIGATOR - "/oracle/apps/menu/root_menu.xml", HOMEPAGE - "/oracle/apps/menu/homepage_menu.xml", PREFERENCE - "/oracle/apps/menu/pref_menu.xml;

setBaseNode

public void setBaseNode(boolean baseNode)
The set method for the baseNode attribute. The menu service stores the MDS layer name information on the menu node. This must be set as a boolean value on the menu item bean. Use node.getCustomizationLayerName() to get the value if it is not null then baseNode = true, it is null then this is a customization node and the baseNode = false. Manage Menu Customization UI used this value to determine if we allow a menu item to be deleted or hidden. Note! this value must be set for all CRUD operations.

Parameters:
baseNode -

isBaseNode

public boolean isBaseNode()
The set method for the baseNode attribute. The menu service stores the MDS layer name information on the menu node. This must be set as a boolean value on the menu item bean. Use node.getCustomizationLayerName() to get the value if it is not null then baseNode = false, it is null then this is a customization node and the baseNode = true. Only a menu item that has been customized will have customizationLayerName set on it. Manage Menu Customization UI used this value to determine if we allow a menu item to be deleted or hidden. Note! this value must be set for all CRUD operations.

Returns:
true or false boolean value

setDirtyNode

public void setDirtyNode(boolean dirtyNode)
The set method for the dirtyNode variable. This is shortcut method used to check if the menu bean has been updated since it was first created. The Manage Menu Customization UI uses this to determine if it should even start an update call to MDS. It is up to developer to keep track of the state of this flag.

deleteMenuEntry

public void deleteMenuEntry()
                     throws oracle.mds.core.MetadataNotFoundException,
                            oracle.mds.naming.ReferenceException,
                            oracle.mds.exception.UnsupportedUpdateException
The helper method used to delete an entry that has been added as part of a customization. The calling code should have already validated that menu item is one added as part of a customization by checking the isBaseNode method. If the item is a base node the calling code should do a updateEntry setting the rendered flag to false. Structure UI has a business rule that states a Group Node with children cannot be deleted. Structure UI code must check the isGroupNodeHasChildren() boolean method before calling delete on a Group Node. Warning! If this check is not done and the groupNode is a not a base node and has children it will be deleted along with all the children.

Throws:
oracle.mds.core.MetadataNotFoundException
oracle.mds.naming.ReferenceException
oracle.mds.exception.UnsupportedUpdateException

setOwnerUI

public void setOwnerUI(java.lang.String ownerUI)
The setter method for the ownerUI attribute. The ownerUI attribute is used by the UI teams to determine which UI was responsible for adding the menu structure as part of a customization. e.g. this menu item was added by APP Composer. The new attribute is required because with the inclusion of FuseCards we need to identify which UI added the menu node and either allow or deny actions on the menu item. e.g. the fuse structure UI cannot delete an item added by APP composer, or Manage Menu Customization cannot delete a menu item added as a FuseCard etc. etc.

Parameters:
ownerUI -

getOwnerUI

public java.lang.String getOwnerUI()
The getter method for the ownerUI attribute. The ownerUI attribute is used by the UI teams to determine which UI was responsible for adding the menu structure as part of a customization. e.g. this menu item was added by APP Composer. The new attribute is required because with the inclusion of FuseCards we need to identify which UI added the menu node and either allow or deny actions on the menu item. e.g. the fuse structure UI cannot delete an item added by APP composer, or Manage Menu Customization cannot delete a menu item added as a FuseCard etc. etc.

Returns:
String.

isGroupNodeHasChildren

public boolean isGroupNodeHasChildren()
                               throws oracle.mds.core.MetadataNotFoundException,
                                      oracle.mds.naming.ReferenceException,
                                      oracle.mds.exception.UnsupportedUpdateException
This method is used to determine if a Group Node has children. Some UI's will only allow the delete of a Group Node if the Group Node does not have children. As some UI's are allowed to delete a group node with children it is up to the calling View code to determine if delete is allowed or not. Warning! If this check is not done and the groupNode is a not a base node and has children it will be deleted along with all the children.

Returns:
true if groupNode does have children false if not.
Throws:
oracle.mds.core.MetadataNotFoundException
oracle.mds.naming.ReferenceException
oracle.mds.exception.UnsupportedUpdateException

public boolean validateDynamicLink()

Returns:

validateStaticLink

public boolean validateStaticLink()
Validate that a menu item of type StaticLink has all required attributes set. Required attributes are label, and destination. The rendered attribute will default to true if not set on the menu item. Due to a bug in the trinidad menu the focusViewId will be set to and empty string even though focusViewId and destination are mutually exclusive.

Returns:
true if set correctly false if not.

Returns:
true if set correctly false if not.
